## Context

Split from 0276 (RDJ-26561 R&R, tracker 0274, remark R1-12): the referee asks
how many duplicates each procedure removes — (1) DOI-based, (2) title+year
matching. This ticket produces the *numbers* as a traceable artifact; 0276
writes the prose that cites them. Split because obtaining the counts may
touch Phase-1 instrumentation (padme, API-dependent, author-coordinated)
while the prose is an ordinary manuscript PR.

## Relevant files

- Phase-1 dedup implementation in `scripts/` (locate the actual dedup step)
- `data/catalogs/run_reports/` — counts may already exist there; check first
- `scripts/schemas.py` — schema if a new CSV artifact is added

## Actions

1. Check existing run reports for per-procedure dedup counts.
2. If absent, instrument the dedup step to log/emit them (per-procedure
   breakdown), coordinating any Phase-1 rerun with the author — never
   triggered from the manuscript build (phase separation).
3. Land the counts as an archived artifact the paper can cite (run report or
   small derived table with a Make target).

## Test

- The artifact regenerates deterministically given the same inputs; counts
  sum consistently with total duplicates removed.

## Verification

- [ ] Counts artifact archived and referenced by path

## Invariants

- Phase separation; no hand-curated numbers.

## Exit criteria

- [ ] Per-procedure dedup counts exist as a pipeline-traceable artifact
- [ ] 0276 unblocked with the artifact path recorded in its body or log
